g freely down her back.  She felt like the princess in the story her mommy had told her, the one who had gone to the ball and met the prince.  She was going to meet better than a prince.  She was going to meet a God.  <br>
<br>
Caedusia reached up and held Sister Semmeline's hand.  It was a little scary going to meet a God.  She wasn't at all sure how to act.  &quot;Sister?&quot;  she whispered.  <br>
<br>
&quot;Shhh.  Just be quiet, child.&quot;<br>
<br>
Caedusia obeyed looking into the temple.  The sounds of the organ echoed in the large chamber.  It was a kind of metallic buzzy sound, not like the instruments they played at the harvest gathering or the spring festival.  It was exciting and chilling and scary and exhilerating all at the same time.  Caedusia looked up at Sister Semmeline, but she was entranced and clearly watching something Caedusia could not see.  <br>
<br>
&quot;It's time, child&quot; the sister whispered and pushed her forward down the aisle to the white marble altar.  Brothers and Sisters filled the temple and all knelt in prayer.  Grandfather Tobias stood behind the altar flanked on either side by a Priestess of Rodcet Nife.  Caedusia looked up at Grandfather Tobias' face.  He had a sharp pointy nose and his eyebrows were thick and shadowed his eyes.  He looked stern like the schoolmaster and she remembered Barthus crying behind the clock, his bum all covered with welts.   She'd given him her cookie to make him feel better.  <br>
<br>
Caedusia stopped and looked back at Sister Semmeline.  The sister nodded her head and shooed Caeudusia forward.  &quot;I'm brave.&quot;  she thought to herself.  &quot;I'm as brave as the second son.&quot;  She continued forward slowly.  &quot;And I do I want Mommy to live and give Daddy a whole parcel of youngun's.&quot;  Caedusia began to climb up the steps.  &quot;I'm brave.&quot;  Step.  &quot;I'm brave.&quot;  Step.  &quot;I'm brave,&quot;  and she knelt before the altar.  <br>
<br>
The organ grew louder and High Father Tobias began to speak &quot;Holy Father Rodcet Nife, we come before you, humble men and women, to serve you.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;We are your servants&quot;  the Brothers and Sisters responded.<br>
<br>
&quot;The plague of Bertoxxulous is once more upon our land and we seek to banish him, as is your will Holy Father Nife.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;We are your servants.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;We ask nothing for ourselves, only to spread the glory of your word and your healing power that Norrath may be rid of darkness and your children may walk in the light forever.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;That your children may walk in the light forever.&quot;<br>
<br>
Grandfather Tobias walked around the alter and stood in front of Caedusia.  &quot;What is your name, child, he asked.<br>
<br>
&quot;Caedusia Talisman&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;And why do you come to this alter today?&quot;<br>
<br>
Caedusia froze a moment in panic searching for the words Sister had told her to say.  She knew she had to get it just right, but now, with everybody looking at her she couldn't remember.  &quot;To make a sacrifice?&quot;   She looked up to the priestess on her right.  The priestess smiled and nodded.  Caedusia heaved a sigh of relief.<br>
<br>
&quot;Go on, child&quot; the father whispered.  <br>
<br>
&quot;To make a sacrifice.  I give my life to Rodcet Nife that he will give life to my mother, Esmira Talisman.&quot;  Caedusia smiled.  She had gotten it right.<br>
<br>
Grandfather Tobias placed his hand on Caedusia's head.  &quot;As the sacrifice is offered from love, let it be recieved in love.  The blessings of our Father be upon you.&quot;<br>
<br>
The priestesses helped Caedusia to her feet and turned her to face the congregation.<br>
Sister Semmeline was the first to come forward and kneel before Caedusia.   &quot;I beseach healing for Esmira Talisman, in the name of Sister Semmeline Tomrow.&quot;  Caedusia placed her hand on Sister Semmeline's head as they had practiced.  &quot;I shall take your prayer with me.&quot;   <br>
<br>
One by one the Brothers and Sisters came and knelt before Caedusia, one by one she placed her hand on their heads and promised to take their prayers with her.  And one by one they filed from the temple.  Caedusia sniffled a little when the last Brother left the temple, leaving her with Grandfather Tobias and the priestesses.  Caedusia's feet hurt from standing still so long and she was tired.   Grandfather Tobias asked her &quot;Are you ready to meet Rodcet Nife, child?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;I'm ready.&quot;  <br>
<br>
The priestesses reached down and lifted Caedusia's dress over her head.  She wore nothing underneath.  They lifted her up onto the alter and lay her down, pulling her dark curls back, away from her neck.  The marble was cold and Caedusia started to shiver.  She looked up at Grandfather Tobias and whispered, &quot;I'm a little scared.&quot;<br>
<br>
Tobias smiled.   &quot;Be brave, lass.&quot;<br>
<br>
The priestesses snuffed out the candles as they left plunging the temple into darkness.    Caedusia began to whimper in the dark.  &quot;I'm brave.&quot; she told herself over and over. &quot;I'm brave.&quot;    <br>
